pick best overall. Which candidate balances? Candidate C has reliability, positive atmosphere, quick decisions, but communication issues and lack of education. For long-distance, crew communication is crucial. Candidate B has technical strengths and stress handling, but interpersonal issues. Candidate A has strong anticipation and leadership but organizational issues. Candidate D strong problem solving but leadership weak.\n\nWe might consider that reliability and crew atmosphere are vital; Candidate C's positive atmosphere and reliability may outweigh communication deficits if can be mitigated. But egocentric and unwilling to further education are concerning for long-term development.\n\nCandidate B's technical and stress handling are strong, but uncooperative may be serious.\n\nWe could ask other agents if they have any additional info on candidate's teamwork or health. But we have all attributes.\n\nWe need to produce a vote. We can either agree with Agent 3 (Candidate B) or propose another. Let's weigh: Candidate B's weaknesses: grumpy, uncooperative. That could be severe for crew. Candidate C's communication difficulty and egocentric may also be severe. Candidate A's unorganized may affect flight planning. Candidate D's arrogance and weak leadership also problematic.\n\nWhich is least problematic? Possibly Candidate B: stress handling and technical competence are critical; interpersonal issues can be trained. So we may vote Candidate B as well.\n\nWe should provide reasoning, referencing attributes. Also note we considered all candidates.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing reasoning and vote.\n\nMETADATA_JSON with vote Candidate B."}
